article(data-role='usage')
  h1 A login example
  p.
    This short example demonstrates the ease of creating simple yet
    efficient login forms. Note that the generated HTML is kept at its
    minimal avoiding as much as possible to include CSS classes for
    positionning elements or animating them.
  .example
    .example1
      p Redish login form
      form
        span.input
          input(type='email', id='username', name='username')
          label(for='username'): span You ID
        span.input
          input(type='password', id='password', name='password')
          label(for='password'): span Your password
        button.small(type='button')
          i.fa.fa-chevron-circle-right.fa-2x
          span Access
    .example2
      p Greenish login form
      form
        span.input
          input(type='email', id='username', name='username')
          label(for='username'): span You ID
        span.input
          input(type='password', id='password', name='password')
          label(for='password'): span Your password
        button.small(type='button')
          i.fa.fa-sign-in.fa-2x
          span Access
  p.
    Both examples rely on the same principles: a set of Stylus file declaring
    functions that you import only if you need them. Each function can be
    customized with your color theme and some plugins are provided to apply
    specific behaviors. Therefore, the generated CSS is strictly limited to
    the style that you have created and imported. No unused CSS rules.
  h1 Usage
  p Add it as a regular package.
  pre: code.bash.
    meteor add pierreeric:creativepure
  p We recommend using the following additional packages:
  pre: code.bash.
    meteor add coffeescript mquandalle:jade mquandalle:stylus fortawesome:fontawesome
  p We now set some global variables in a Stylus file.
  pre: code.stylus.
    // Base path for Creative & Pure
    basePath = '.meteor/local/build/programs/web.browser/packages/pierreeric_creativepure/styles/%s'

    // Global variables
    roundCorner =     3px
    buttonSmallSize = 70px

    // Main colors
    brandColor =    #dd7c27
    textColor =     darken(brandColor, 70%)
    bgColor =       lighten(brandColor, 90%)
    brandPrimary =  brandColor
    brandDanger =   hsl(0, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))
    brandWarning =  hsl(45, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))
    brandSuccess =  hsl(120, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))
    brandInfo =     hsl(240, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))

    // Breakpoints using Rupture
    maxSize = 960px
    rupture.scale = 0 600px 800px maxSize
    rupture.scale-names = 'small' 'medium' 'desktop' 'hd'

    // Fonts for Typographic
    monoFont = optima
    fontSize()
      font-size 11px
      +above('small')
        font-size @font-size + 1
      +above('medium')
        font-size @font-size + 2
      +above('desktop')
        font-size @font-size + 3
      +above('hd')
        font-size @font-size + 4

    // Default transition values
    defaultTransitionValue = .3s ease-out
  p And we are ready to GO.
